### Default Constructor

Every class has a default constructor (no arguments) if no constructor is defined.

```dart
class Point {
  int x = 0;
  int y = 0;
}

void main() {
  var p = Point(); // Uses default constructor
  print('${p.x}, ${p.y}');
}
```

### Parameterized Constructor

```dart
class Point {
  int x;
  int y;

  // Standard constructor
  Point(int x, int y) {
    this.x = x;
    this.y = y;
  }
}

void main() {
  var p = Point(3, 4);
}
```

### Constructor with Initializing Formal Parameters

Dart provides a shorthand syntax for assigning parameters to fields:

```dart
class Point {
  int x;
  int y;

  // Initializing formal parameters
  Point(this.x, this.y);
}
```

### Constructor with Named Parameters

```dart
class Person {
  String name;
  int age;
  String? email;

  Person({
    required this.name,
    required this.age,
    this.email,
  });
}

void main() {
  var p = Person(name: 'Alice', age: 30, email: 'alice@example.com');
}
```

### Initializer List

```dart
class Point {
  int x;
  int y;

  Point.fromCoordinates(Map<String, int> coords)
      : x = coords['x'] ?? 0,
        y = coords['y'] ?? 0;
}
```

### Const Constructor

```dart
class ImmutablePoint {
  final int x;
  final int y;

  const ImmutablePoint(this.x, this.y);
}

void main() {
  const p = ImmutablePoint(0, 0);
}
```

### Factory Constructor

```dart
class Logger {
  static final Map<String, Logger> _cache = {};
  final String name;

  factory Logger(String name) {
    return _cache.putIfAbsent(name, () => Logger._internal(name));
  }

  Logger._internal(this.name);
}
```

> **Key Point:** Use initializing formal parameters (`this.x`) for simple field assignment. Use initializer lists for validation or more complex initialization logic.

codeExample:
class Rectangle {
  double width;
  double height;

  // Primary constructor
  Rectangle(this.width, this.height);

  // Initializer list constructor
  Rectangle.square(double side)
      : width = side,
        height = side;

  // Named parameter constructor
  Rectangle.fromDimensions({required this.width, required this.height});

  double get area => width * height;
}

void main() {
  var r1 = Rectangle(10, 5);
  var r2 = Rectangle.square(7);
  var r3 = Rectangle.fromDimensions(width: 8, height: 3);

  print('Rectangle areas: ${r1.area}, ${r2.area}, ${r3.area}');
}
